          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_BudgetGroupsRetrieve",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve budget group information from a database. It allows filtering based on budget group ID, provider ID, and energy type. The procedure queries a view named "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "BudgetApp_vwBudgetGroups",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and optionally filters results based on the provided parameters. It also includes a UNION operation that appends a default row with a BudgetGroupID of 0 and an Active status of 'TRUE'."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves conditional logic, subqueries, and a UNION operation, which adds a moderate level of complexity. The use of multiple parameters and conditional filtering increases the complexity compared to a simple SELECT statement."
        }
      ]
    },
